            <h2>HTTP Server Basics</h2>
            <p>Creating HTTP servers with Node.js http module.</p>
            
            <h3>Simple HTTP Server</h3>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre><code>import http from 'http';

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' });
  res.end('Hello from Node.js!');
});

server.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server running on port 3000');
});</code></pre>
            </div>
            
            <div class="key-points">
                <h3>Key Concepts:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>http.createServer():</strong> Creates HTTP server</li>
                    <li><strong>Request handler:</strong> Function that handles each request</li>
                    <li><strong>Response object:</strong> Used to send response to client</li>
                    <li><strong>Non-blocking:</strong> Server handles multiple requests concurrently</li>
                    <li><strong>Event-driven:</strong> Uses event loop for request handling</li>
                </ul>
